––– output –––
30000
––– comment –––
For both operators below, the untimed result set is the reference answer.
The timed query may stop early, but it must not introduce ids that are absent from the untimed answer.
Any id present only in the timed result is a timeout leak.
––– input –––
query='@doc \"AA A28\" NOTNEAR/3 (BB|CC|DD|EE|FF|GG|HH|II|JJ|KK|LL|MM|NN|OO|PP|QQ|RR|SS|TT|UU|VV|WW|XX|YY|ZZ|w1|w2|w3|w4|w5|w6|w7|a1|a2|a3|a4|a5|a6|a7|a8|a9|a10|a11|a12|a85|a86|a87)'
mysql -N -h0 -P9306 -e "select id from test3 where match('$query') order by id asc limit 1000 option threads=1, max_matches=5000, max_query_time=2000;" | sort > /tmp/issue-4375-notnear-reference.txt
mysql -N -h0 -P9306 -e "select id from test3 where match('$query') order by id asc limit 1000 option threads=1, max_matches=5000, max_query_time=1; show warnings;" > /tmp/issue-4375-notnear-timed.raw
grep -E '^[0-9]+$' /tmp/issue-4375-notnear-timed.raw | sort > /tmp/issue-4375-notnear-timed.txt
comm -23 /tmp/issue-4375-notnear-timed.txt /tmp/issue-4375-notnear-reference.txt > /tmp/issue-4375-notnear-leaks.txt
if [ -s /tmp/issue-4375-notnear-leaks.txt ]; then echo leaked; cat /tmp/issue-4375-notnear-leaks.txt; else echo subset-ok; fi
––– output –––
subset-ok
––– input –––
query='@doc \"AA A28\" -\"A54 A52\"'
mysql -N -h0 -P9306 -e "select id from test3 where match('$query') order by id asc limit 1000 option threads=1, max_matches=5000, max_query_time=2000;" | sort > /tmp/issue-4375-andnot-reference.txt
mysql -N -h0 -P9306 -e "select id from test3 where match('$query') order by id asc limit 1000 option threads=1, max_matches=5000, max_query_time=2; show warnings;" > /tmp/issue-4375-andnot-timed.raw
grep -E '^[0-9]+$' /tmp/issue-4375-andnot-timed.raw | sort > /tmp/issue-4375-andnot-timed.txt
comm -23 /tmp/issue-4375-andnot-timed.txt /tmp/issue-4375-andnot-reference.txt > /tmp/issue-4375-andnot-leaks.txt
if [ -s /tmp/issue-4375-andnot-leaks.txt ]; then echo leaked; cat /tmp/issue-4375-andnot-leaks.txt; else echo subset-ok; fi
